<br>
The calender will mean nothing unless a precident can be set.  Each of us are going on old rules for old servers, those in no way match how another server worked.  Our guilds policy is to only schedule planes, everything else being first come, first serve.  A similar thing happened on Nameless shortly after it came up Q4 99, Q1 00.  The leaders of the guilds that were doing the conflicted zones/mobs decided on a loose system.  The system was simple and made sense.  Only planes can be reserved, others are only intentions and are not to be considered reservations.  It remains to this day.  <br>
<br>
This isnt just about 2 dragons, its about any mob/zone.  I believe it certainly should be discussed among the conflicting guilds guildleaders to prevent any future conflict, but its their iniative to take.  If they decide that they will respect the others schedules of anything from a plane camp to a mob like frog king/tirenna then so be it.<br>
<br>
If those guilds want to be at each others throats for the next year or two, so be it, but I doubt any of them want that.<br>
<br>
Whatever they do, the ability of anyone to make a reservation for anyone, needs to be addressed.  Wether it is controlled to registered guild leaders, or what, something needs to be done.<br>
<br>
