<br>
We also wish to work extensively with other guilds to make sure we do not step on others toes and make a system to make it fair for all.<br>
<br>
The first come first serve approach is a poor one in relation to dragons.  There is great precendent on other servers for using the schedule for dragons.  I can guarantee you that if you keep this position on the dragons that it will cause much more trouble than just working with others to schedule them.  This is no threat - there is no reason for one.  I am just merely pointing out that I think it will hurt your guild in the long run if you keep that position. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
It doesn't matter which guild is the most powerful guild on the server.  The real challenge is: how long will your guild last?  If run correctly it can last an awful long time.  If run poorly, the guild can collapse and members will flock to greener pastures.<br>
<br>
Again, we stress peace and friendship with all the guilds on the server.  There is plenty to compete for in this game, but lets not let our competitive nature overcome our humanity.<br>
