<br>
Fuck Sacred Fires.  Fuck Promethian Order.  Fuck In Virtue.  Fuck Caer Cadarn.  Fuck En Media Res.  Fuck Sliver.  Fuck Agony.  Fuck every guild with more than 10 people over level 40.  Fuck this bullshit about might equals right.  It doesn't.  Some of you may play Everquest to prove how much better you are than other people.  Maybe you were picked on as a child.  Maybe your mother loved your sister best.  Too bad.  Get some fucking therapy so you can leave that shit behind when you log-in.<br>
<br>
Me?  Yeah, I'm a member of PO.  Big fucking deal.  I love my guild.  We do great things.  But frankly, this issue doesn't have shit to do with us.  In a sense, it doesn't have shit to do with SF either.  In good time both guilds can kill uber_fucking_fuckmob_fuckteen 27 fucking times.  let me clue you in on something, though.<br>
<br>
Everyone isn't in one of the large guilds.  I know this may come as a surprise to some of you, but there are actually other people who play this game.  That's right, all those avatars you see walking around are controlled by another actual human behind a screen somewhere.  And here's the kicker--you're not more special than they are.  Their mothers may even have loved them a little bit more.<br>
<br>
Before I came to this server, I was always part of smaller, usually mid-level guilds and I guess I still see things from that perspective, and here's how this looks to me:<br>
<br>
-***-<br>
<br>
Small_Guild_03: &quot;Hey, why are you uberguilds always fighting?&quot;<br>
Uber_Guild_02: &quot;Because we have to prove we're better and more special and more important and have bigger cocks than all the other guilds on this server.&quot;<br>
SG3: &quot;But why?&quot;<br>
UG2: &quot;You wouldn't understand you fucking pissant, get out of my face.&quot;<br>
SG3: &quot;But we want to get together with Small_Guild_05 and Small_Guild_12 to arrange a Naggy raid and we need to be able to schedule a time to hit Naggy when everyone can be there...&quot;<br>
UG2: &quot;You want to hit Naggy?  Ha!  If you don't have the manpower to take Naggy down the second he pops then you're just out of fucking luck.&quot;<br>
SG3: &quot;But some of our guild has wanted to kill Naggy for years now and never gotten the chance...&quot;<br>
UG2: &quot;Cry me a big fat fucking river.  Ever read Dr. Suess when you were a child?  Remember the story about the Starbellies?  Well we have stars and you fucking don't and there's no machine to get a star here.  We're more important and special than you.  Obviously if you're not in our guild you're not only a complete fuckface but you're also a bad player.  And you're n00bish attitude of actually wanting to kill ubermobs that only we have sovereign right to is annoying me.  Fuck off.&quot;<br>
SG3: &quot;Well could you at least post on the calendar when you're killing stuff so we can try and get together a group to kill Naggy on repop?&quot;<br>
UG2: &quot;NO!  God damnit, I thought I explained to you that only we're allowed to kill ubermobs.  If we posted on the calendar people like you might do like you said and steal our kill.  FFA is a misnomer.  It's supposed to be FFU--Fucking For Us.&quot;<br>
SG3: &quot;... Well, can we at least send a couple people along on your raids for a shot at quest drops?&quot;<br>
UG2: &quot;Fuck no!  You're all n00bz and l0s3rz if you're not in our guild.  You just create lag.  And they're OUR items anyway.  Now, if you'll excuse me, I have to go farm some stuff which is incredibly green to me so that I can turn around and sell its items to the same people I just KS'd it from.&quot;<br>
<br>
-***-<br>
<br>
The calendar isn't for those of us lucky enough to be in powerful guilds.  Sure, it helps prevent us from butting heads which is a noble cause in and of itself, but we don't _need_ it to accomplish things.  However, there are 2000 people on Vazaelle at peak hours.  Maybe 200 of those belong to powerful guilds.  That's 1/10 of the server population.  That means 90% of the people who potentially want to kill an ubermob do not have those resources at their disposal.  They have to coordinate to kill an ubermob and that's why we must maintain a calendar.  The big guilds can and should discuss a rotation for ubermobs, and they should post the results on the calendar.  Whether or not you believe ubermobs can be scheduled, at least post your intentions on the calendar for the sake of those who don't have infolines set up with the big guilds.  I mean, does it really _hurt_ you if you post your plans on the calendar?  After all, you should have already talked with the other big guilds such that they won't gank it from you.<br>
<br>
Have a little respect for _everyone_ on the server.  We're all people and we deserve at least that.<br>
<br>
....and if you think just you're more important than someone else just because you have  a guildtag over your head or you come from uber_server_05 where you had 87 level 63 necros, fuck you. <p><p><center><img src="http://www-scf.usc.edu/~rabiega/sigs/slansig2.jpg"><br><i>Sslanis Soulforge<br>Just Another Dead Lizard</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucarrais.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carrais</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/9/01 12:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I don't usually rant but...</span><hr size=1> Kaedaian,<br>
<br>
I was quite honest in what I said, no sarcasm intended. On a personal level, I have to agree with Sotae. The level window on Naggy/Vox is too small to let them sit till someone is ready to kill them, especially when theres only 2 guilds capable of doing so. Faster killings = more spawns. I know you guys are in the same boat as us, and as of Wednesday night, we are done with those two dragons.<br>
<br>
As for scheduling, I would certianly like to see guild leaders work out an agreement. We can make a passworded calendar here, or at least try to. Right now I think the problem is, if we make it passworded, then only guild leaders can post OR view it. Nobody else would be able to read the calendar. If anyone knows a calendar that we can use that can only be posted on with a password, and can be viewed without, please let us know.<br>
<br>
But what do we want here? Are we only talking about Naggy and Vox? Or do we want to reserve every single large scale encounter we ever do in the game, just cause we're afraid someone else might beat us to it? Honestly I don't think its possible. I can see it happening for Nag/Vox possibly but things like Trakanon, VS, velious dragons, lodizal, KD, etc I don't really think so..<br>
<br>
Clearly there is logic behind our view, but you are right in that we cannot dictate how things will be done on Vazaelle. IF we come to an agreement, great. We can honor that. What I'm afraid of is the lack of honesty displayed quite often on this server so far. We as a server can make a system, but how many will adhere to it? And I mean soundly adhere, not with half-truths and political nonsense. That is for Congress, not for EQ. We're here to have fun, so lets make the game better.<br>
<br>
Carrais Tal`Amrith<br>
